snippet.title: Aquaman (2018) | Official Trailer Final# Jason Momoa, Amber Heard, Nicole Kidman
snippet.description:
SYNOPSIS:
Arthur Curry learns that he is the heir to the underwater kingdom of Atlantis, and must step forward to lead his people and be a hero to the world.

From Warner Bros. Pictures and director James Wan comes an action-packed adventure that spans the vast, visually breathtaking underwater world of the seven seas, Aquaman, starring Jason Momoa in the title role. The film reveals the origin story of half-human, half-Atlantean Arthur Curry and takes him on the journey of his lifetime—one that will not only force him to face who he really is, but to discover if he is worthy of who he was born to be…a king.

The film also stars Amber Heard (Justice League, Magic Mike XXL) as Mera, a fierce warrior and Aquaman’s ally throughout his journey; Oscar nominee Willem Dafoe (Platoon, Spider-Man 2) as Vulko, council to the Atlantean throne; Patrick Wilson (The Conjuring films, Watchmen) as Orm/Ocean Master, the present King of Atlantis; Dolph Lundgren (The Expendables films), King of the Atlantean tribe Xebel; Yahya Abdul-Mateen II (upcoming Baywatch, Netflix’s The Get Down) as the vengeful Black Manta; and Oscar winner Nicole Kidman (The Hours, Lion) as Arthur’s mom, Atlanna; as well as Ludi Lin (Power Rangers) as Captain Murk, Atlantean Commando; and Temuera Morrison (Star Wars: Episode II – Attack of the Clones, Green Lantern) as Arthur’s dad, Tom Curry.

Wan directs from a screenplay by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick (The Conjuring 2) and Will Beall (Gangster Squad, TV’s Training Day), story by Geoff Johns & James Wan and Will Beall, based on characters from DC, Aquaman created by Paul Norris and Mort Weisinger. The film is produced by Peter Safran and Rob Cowan, with Deborah Snyder, Zack Snyder, Jon Berg, Geoff Johns and Walter Hamada serving as executive producers.

Wan’s team behind the scenes includes such frequent collaborators as Oscar-nominated director of photography Don Burgess (The Conjuring 2, Forrest Gump), his five-time editor Kirk Morri (The Conjuring films, Furious 7, the Insidious films), and production designer Bill Brzeski (Furious 7). They are joined by costume designer Kym Barrett (The Matrix trilogy, The Amazing Spider-Man) and composer Rupert Gregson-Williams (Wonder Woman).

Warner Bros. Pictures Presents a Safran Company Production, a James Waan Film, Aquaman. The film is set to hit theaters on December 21, 2018 in 3D and 2D and IMAX, and will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures, a Warner Bros. Entertainment Company.

snippet.title: Gal Gadot e Amber Heard, gara di bellezza per Justice League
snippet.description:
(KIKA) - LOS ANGELES - Una splendida Amber Heard si è presa la scena sul red carpet della premiere di Justice League, il nuovo film diretto da Zack Snyder e Josh Whedon che sarà ambientato nei momenti immediatamente successivi alle vicende narrate in Batman vs Superman: Dawn of Justice e uscirà in italia il 16 novembre.

L'ex compagna di Johnny Depp e Elon Musk si è presentata sul tappeto rosso con un lungo abito della collezione Versace che in quanto a sensualità ha dato del filo da torcere a Gal Gadot, in oro firmata Altuzarra Spring 2018 RTW

La pellicola ha riportato sul set il trio composto da Ben Affleck nei panni di Batman, Henry Cavill in quelli di Superman e la bellissima Gal Gadot alias Wonder Woman. Accanto a loro, lotterà uno squadrone di fedelissimi DC, composto da Aquaman, interpretato da Jason Momoa, Flash impersonato da Ezra Miller e Ray Fisher nelle vesti di Cyborg.

snippet.title: Justice League – First look at Amber Heard as Mera
snippet.description:
Justice League – First look at Amber Heard as Mera

It’s all or nothing at this point for Warner Bros. and DC Comics with their cinematic superhero universe. It’s not as if their films haven’t been financially successful so far, but they’ve taken a critical bludgeoning at the box office thanks to rampant studio inteference and an unclear direction. Justice League on the other hand, is looking to change all that. Zack Snyder’s big team-up movie is going to feature all manner of heroes, from brutal billionaires who get confused for owls through to titanc tsunami crushers of the deep.
And a few supporting characters added to the mix as well. IGN revealed the first look at Aquaman’s greatest ally, as Amber Heard suited up in some regal armour for a smackdown:

Damn, that looks utterly fantastic. Say what you like about Snyder, but his production usually includes some utterly fantastic costume design. In the DC Comics source material, Mera happens to be the wife of Aquaman and queen of Atlantis. She’s also a formidable fighter, able to match blows with heavyweight foes thanks to her unique biology that allows her to survive the crushing pressure of the ocean depths.
But it’s her skill with Hydrokinesis that really makes her dangerous. Mera can increase the density of water around her, essentially hardening it and reshaping it into various combat-effective shapes which she can smash into enemies. She’s basically a waterbender then. Anyway, that’s a fantastic first look at the Atlantean queen, although don’t expect her to have too much of a role to play in Justice League.

Amber Heard’s Mera will however, be far more prominent in James Wan’s Aquaman movie, which kicks off filming next year. As for Justice League, that’s currently still on track for a November 2017 release. And hopefully it doesn’t blow its reveal load before then with too much hype this time. Nothing wrong with keeping a few of those reveals secret, ya dig?

snippet.title: ✅  Johnny Depp et Amber Heard : ce nouveau procès à 50 millions de dollars
snippet.description:
💖 Please Subscribe: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCVBZ7bN9BPx3LkMkWSMQL1g?sub_confirmation=1
✍ C'est reparti ! Ce 28 juillet se clôturait le procès de Johnny Depp contre le Sun à Londres.  L'acteur de Pirates des Caraïbes poursuivait le tabloid britannique qui l'avait qualifié d'"homme qui bat sa femme" dans un article.  Son ex-femme, Amber Heard, est venue y témoigner en qualité de témoin, faisant pleuvoir les sordides révélations sur leur houleuse histoire lors de ce procès très médiatique.  Selon le rapporte le Daily Mail, le verdict n'est pas attendu avant septembre.  De quoi signer la fin de cette bataille judiciaire ? Pas vraiment ! Comme le rappelle le journal, un autre procès s'ouvrira l'an prochain.  .C'est cette fois de l'autre côté de l'Atlantique que se déroulera la procédure.  Johnny Depp a déposé une plainte pour diffamation envers Amber Heard, suite à sa tribune publiée dans le Washington Post.  S'il n'y est pas cité explicitement, l'acteur estime qu'il est évident que l'article se réfère à lui et que son image a été salie.  Il réclame donc la somme de 50 millions ...
💖 #AffaireHeardDepp, #procès, #Justice
